title: ULA’s Delta 4 prepares for final West Coast launch as Vandenberg seeks new tenants
summary: After completing the NROL-91 mission, ULA will start vacating SLC-6 and consolidate operations at SLC-3

title: Last West Coast Delta IV Heavy to launch with NROL-91
summary: United Launch Alliance’s (ULA) Delta IV Heavy rocket will make its last West Coast launch on Saturday, carrying out a mission for the National Reconnaissance Office, as it moves one flight closer to retirement. Liftoff of the NRO Launch 91 (NROL-91) mission from Space Launch Complex 6 — at the Vandenberg Space Force Base in California — is expected to take place at 2:53 PM PDT (21:53 UTC).
